  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "An earthquake hits West Sumatra",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "An earthquake measuring 6.4 on the Richter scale shook the island of West Sumatra in Indonesia. Padang city is said to have been heavily damaged by the earthquake.",
        "In addition, the Indonesian media reports that the earthquake damaged the city of Padang on Siberut Island in West Sumatra.",
        "It is also said that this earthquake that happened yesterday (29) is one of a series of earthquakes.",
        "There were no casualties from the earthquake that occurred yesterday (29). However, as there was a risk of aftershocks, people were evacuated from unsafe places."
      ],
